  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aims of this study are twofold: (1) to develop an innovative approach for studying brain
      glucose metabolism using functional diffusion weighted imaging (DWI) and BOLD fMRI in humans;
      (2) to evaluate the effect of short peripheral electrical stimulation (PES) treatment on
      brain and brain-stem targets, associated with control of food intake and energy expenditure,
      in response to glucose stimuli, in healthy volunteers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
